WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.719 --> 00:00:02.273
Well, good evening, family.

00:00:02.273 --> 00:00:05.085
Thank you for joining us again today.

00:00:05.496 --> 00:00:07.159
We're going to pray tonight.

00:00:07.159 --> 00:00:10.559
I want to pray more than talk.

00:00:10.559 --> 00:00:18.880
And so, I want to go over some of the things we have in the news since I've been with you last.

00:00:18.880 --> 00:00:22.840
There's a lot going on, as everybody can see.

00:00:23.600 --> 00:00:26.640
Paris is on fire.

00:00:27.488 --> 00:00:35.314
If you all remember, I saw the Eiffel Tower on fire and I said, 'It's burning.

00:00:35.314 --> 00:00:37.130
' And I don't know why it's burning.

00:00:37.130 --> 00:00:40.079
I see it burning, and there are people rioting.

00:00:40.079 --> 00:00:43.146
They're going nuts in the streets, and the Eiffel Tower is on fire.

00:00:43.146 --> 00:00:47.560
And I said, 'I don't know how you burn metal, because the Eiffel Tower is metal.

00:00:47.560 --> 00:00:50.160
' But I saw it burning.

00:00:50.160 --> 00:01:01.013
And so we see over the weekend people acting crazy in France and burning the Eiffel Tower, just like the Lord showed us.

00:01:02.026 --> 00:01:03.760
Was it last year?

00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:04.879
Yeah, two years ago.

00:01:04.879 --> 00:01:05.172
Two years ago.

00:01:05.759 --> 00:01:06.933
It's been a while.

00:01:06.933 --> 00:01:12.907
But I saw the Eiffel Tower burning, and I said, 'I don't know what causes the Eiffel Tower to burn.

00:01:12.907 --> 00:01:15.860
' And I still don't understand how that could burn—it's metal.

00:01:15.860 --> 00:01:18.240
But I guess it's on the bottom.

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:21.496
Maybe they lit some tires on fire or something.

00:01:21.496 --> 00:01:24.539
But there it is, just like the vision.

00:01:24.539 --> 00:01:26.100
I saw it burning.

00:01:26.100 --> 00:01:26.490
Yeah.

00:01:26.880 --> 00:01:28.720
It's on the side of it, isn't it, honey?

00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:29.360
Yeah.

00:01:29.360 --> 00:01:31.866
So, it's not the Eiffel Tower itself; it's metal.

00:01:31.866 --> 00:01:36.320
I was thinking, because that's in the vision, I thought, 'How in the world does a metal structure burn?

00:01:36.320 --> 00:01:36.693
' Yeah.

00:01:36.693 --> 00:01:39.520
And then, so they're burning tires or something.

00:01:39.520 --> 00:01:41.600
Yeah.

00:01:41.600 --> 00:01:43.662
And that's what I saw in the spirit.

00:01:43.662 --> 00:01:47.1000
And so they're popping fireworks, and they're rioting, and doing...

00:01:48.320 --> 00:01:50.160
I said, 'Everything is burning.

00:01:50.160 --> 00:01:52.667
' I told everybody, I said, 'This is what I see.

00:01:52.667 --> 00:01:55.040
I see everything is burning in France.

00:01:55.040 --> 00:01:58.039
' I see things burning, people acting nuts.

00:01:58.039 --> 00:02:01.200
And this is what has been happening.

00:02:01.200 --> 00:02:07.224
Two years ago, they're burning everything up just like I saw there.

00:02:07.224 --> 00:02:10.302
I saw things in trash cans.

00:02:10.302 --> 00:02:11.476
I saw things...

00:02:11.867 --> 00:02:22.160
and what's amazing is it took two years for that word to come to pass, and I said, 'Black swan events are coming.

00:02:23.599 --> 00:02:24.971
This will be on purpose.

00:02:24.971 --> 00:02:26.987
' They're going to try to do this.

00:02:27.280 --> 00:02:33.670
This is something, and I saw major events starting to really take place in Europe, especially France.

00:02:33.670 --> 00:02:44.309
And it was down the river there, and Emmanuel Macron was riding on a black swan.

00:02:44.319 --> 00:02:46.140
So here they are, they're doing it.

00:02:46.140 --> 00:02:47.680
I don't know why they're doing this.

00:02:47.680 --> 00:02:48.879
It's over football.

00:02:48.879 --> 00:02:50.720
Oh, football, soccer.

00:02:50.720 --> 00:02:52.560
Are they happy or are they mad?

00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:52.880
They're mad.

00:02:53.200 --> 00:02:55.333
They're mad about what happened.

00:02:55.333 --> 00:02:55.760
Yeah.

00:02:55.760 --> 00:02:58.640
Mad about who won.

00:02:58.640 --> 00:03:00.491
I was disappointed with my Thunder.

00:03:00.491 --> 00:03:01.143
They lost.

00:03:01.143 --> 00:03:02.857
I was disappointed with that.

00:03:02.857 --> 00:03:08.480
But we knew that when I saw Wemby and his face dominant, I knew.

00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:13.599
But I don't talk about sports and that.

00:03:14.319 --> 00:03:18.159
Go ahead and show what else.

00:03:18.159 --> 00:03:22.800
Yeah, and then you have to go over.

00:03:22.800 --> 00:03:29.270
Okay, I want you to talk about the tunnels.

00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:29.650
Yeah.

00:03:29.650 --> 00:03:30.020
Okay.

00:03:30.020 --> 00:03:39.920
So, we had a major boom, an asteroid, a meteor go over Pennsylvania and North Carolina, and it was loud.

00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:42.720
Can you play that clip?

00:03:42.720 --> 00:03:50.639
So, the Lord showed us several times that this will be, as of April the 1st, signs from the heavens.

00:03:50.639 --> 00:04:01.200
And He said, 'You're about to see major signs from the heavens, and there will be meteors and like asteroids, and they're coming.

00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:13.360
' And I heard major loud noises that were like sonic booms, but some of them that are coming are so loud that they will break the glass out of people's homes.

00:04:13.360 --> 00:04:15.720
They'll break the glass out of people's cars.

00:04:15.720 --> 00:04:19.979
It was so loud for something that is coming.

00:04:19.979 --> 00:04:24.720
And I said, 'This will start on April 1st.

00:04:24.720 --> 00:04:26.460
This will start on April 1st.

00:04:26.460 --> 00:04:36.853
' And the Lord said, 'Watch this time frame going into Rosh Hashanah into September, and then more acceleration will come on 9/11.

00:04:36.853 --> 00:04:38.160
' The Harbingers.

00:04:38.160 --> 00:04:41.840
Now, this just happened Friday.

00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:43.640
Yeah, it did.

00:04:43.640 --> 00:04:44.240
Yeah.

00:04:44.240 --> 00:04:44.880
Go ahead.

00:04:44.880 --> 00:04:46.800
And what is this one, hun?

00:04:46.800 --> 00:04:50.359
This is just a clip of people hearing it.

00:04:50.359 --> 00:04:53.355
Okay, go ahead.

00:04:53.355 --> 00:04:57.350
Let them hear it.

00:04:57.360 --> 00:05:04.230
Did it already happen?

00:05:04.240 --> 00:05:06.000
It sounds like a gunshot, doesn't it?

00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:09.600
Yeah, that's the one in the day.

00:05:09.600 --> 00:05:10.880
Yeah, you can see it.

00:05:10.880 --> 00:05:14.870
Look at it falling.

00:05:14.880 --> 00:05:15.480
Is it?

00:05:16.080 --> 00:05:17.280
Yeah.

00:05:17.280 --> 00:05:17.943
No reports.

00:05:17.943 --> 00:05:22.629
A sonic boom in South Carolina.

00:05:22.639 --> 00:05:27.184
The community around Columbia, nearby counties shaken and startled from the noise.

00:05:27.184 --> 00:05:33.253
The US Geological Survey confirming this was not an earthquake, but no word yet on what caused it.

00:05:33.253 --> 00:05:35.840
No reports of injuries or damage.

00:05:35.840 --> 00:05:41.189
Mysterious.

00:05:41.199 --> 00:05:41.908
That's amazing.

00:05:41.908 --> 00:05:43.680
It looks like a flash.

00:05:43.680 --> 00:05:45.120
Yeah.

00:05:45.120 --> 00:05:51.840
So, but the Lord warned us it would start on April 1st and it would go clear into the summer, all these months ahead.

00:05:51.840 --> 00:05:56.720
And He said this would be shakings of signs in the heavens.

00:05:56.720 --> 00:05:59.600
And so we're seeing it.

00:05:59.600 --> 00:06:00.880
Interesting though, huh?

00:06:00.880 --> 00:06:02.720
Yes.

00:06:02.720 --> 00:06:07.600
You can kind of see it really went over Boston really loud.

00:06:07.600 --> 00:06:12.720
See it go over Boston.

00:06:14.560 --> 00:06:20.390
There were people freaking out in Boston because it was really loud over Boston.

00:06:20.400 --> 00:06:21.840
Okay.

00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:29.440
I was going to do that.

00:06:29.440 --> 00:06:30.400
Do what?

00:06:30.400 --> 00:06:31.120
You want this one?

00:06:31.120 --> 00:06:31.787
Yep.

00:06:31.787 --> 00:06:33.120
Go ahead.

00:06:33.120 --> 00:06:33.582
Okay.

00:06:33.582 --> 00:06:37.884
When I saw the three banks, I saw the river.

00:06:37.884 --> 00:06:39.698
Do you remember what I saw?

00:06:39.698 --> 00:06:41.520
I saw Jamie Dimon.

00:06:43.039 --> 00:06:44.747
I saw Chase Bank.

00:06:46.382 --> 00:06:46.667
I saw Wells Fargo.

00:06:55.792 --> 00:06:56.048
And I saw Bank of America.

00:06:59.912 --> 00:07:00.208
This part of it, I want to say this is not financial advice.

00:07:10.720 --> 00:07:11.190
This is all in my opinion.

00:07:11.190 --> 00:07:14.679
I am not a financial adviser, okay?

00:07:15.480 --> 00:07:22.749
This is just what I see in vision, and I can miss it.

00:07:22.749 --> 00:07:32.400
But I want to tell you, I saw this man back in February, and he was at a brook, at a table.

00:07:32.400 --> 00:07:36.920
There was a table, and they were coming to an agreement.

00:07:36.920 --> 00:07:45.199
But he said, in this, 'I saw three major banks'—him, the guy over here, and this is Chase Bank, I believe, right?

00:07:45.199 --> 00:07:45.759
Yeah.

00:07:45.759 --> 00:07:47.600
Bank of America and Wells Fargo.

00:07:55.419 --> 00:07:55.809
They were in it together, and they were upset about crypto.

00:07:56.979 --> 00:07:58.354
They didn't want it to happen.

00:08:02.864 --> 00:08:03.080
They wanted to be the boss.

00:08:05.028 --> 00:08:07.199
So they took a rope and they tied it around Crypto.

00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:27.733
And Crypto was in the form of a rocket, and they wrapped it around this rocket, and they had a rope to it, and he was the head of it.

00:08:27.733 --> 00:08:39.920
He was the head of it, and he would pull it down, and he would let it go way high, and he would pull down.

00:08:42.169 --> 00:08:42.338
And there was a great manipulation.

00:08:42.338 --> 00:08:49.300
If they can't stop it, they will manipulate it so that you won't trust it.

00:08:49.300 --> 00:08:55.408
And I saw that they would not be able to stop it, so they would manipulate it.

00:08:58.855 --> 00:08:59.183
But then I heard Garlinghouse say, 'All we need is clarity.

00:08:59.183 --> 00:09:02.453
' And he was excited; he wanted clarity.

00:09:02.453 --> 00:09:04.983
It was a black line.

00:09:04.983 --> 00:09:07.867
It was black as onyx again.

00:09:07.867 --> 00:09:09.829
Black as onyx.

00:09:09.829 --> 00:09:13.552
Think about the symbolization here again.

00:09:30.902 --> 00:09:31.371
It was black as onyx.

00:09:31.371 --> 00:09:33.839
There's something here.

00:09:33.839 --> 00:09:38.532
Garlinghouse said, 'All we need is clarity.

00:09:38.532 --> 00:09:43.474
' And the rocket that was manipulated by the rope broke.

00:09:57.449 --> 00:09:57.733
It broke.

00:10:05.314 --> 00:10:05.509
And the rocket took off in the sky, and you couldn't see it no more.

00:10:05.509 --> 00:10:06.286
It went away.

00:10:06.853 --> 00:10:08.347
It went into the clouds.

00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:14.560
And I watched that as they tried to manipulate it, and the rope broke, and it went as high.

00:10:19.489 --> 00:10:19.699
It went...

00:10:21.671 --> 00:10:21.813
it was...

00:10:25.759 --> 00:10:26.079
I was like, 'Look at that.

00:10:26.079 --> 00:10:30.631
' But as I watched that in that vision, I saw BlackRock in the distance, and BlackRock wasn't in with these three bankers.

00:10:30.631 --> 00:10:31.688
They were off to the side.

00:10:31.688 --> 00:10:38.230
So, if you go to the other ones, I saw the senators, you know, like insider trading stuff, like you already know what's going to happen.

00:11:00.800 --> 00:11:01.440
So, you have your bags packed, and I saw certain things that would make Pelosi look like a boy scout.

00:11:01.440 --> 00:11:08.720
So, let's go ahead and hear what this Jamie Dimon has to say about crypto.

00:11:08.720 --> 00:11:11.080
He's not happy.

00:11:19.531 --> 00:11:19.908
Go ahead.

00:11:19.908 --> 00:11:25.742
So, are you happy with the way the Clarity Act is turning out?

00:11:25.742 --> 00:11:26.773
No.

00:11:26.773 --> 00:11:27.804
No.

00:11:27.804 --> 00:11:36.160
Because it allows them to effectively pay interest on deposits, stablecoins or something like that, without the protection that they should have.

00:11:43.680 --> 00:11:44.080
And it doesn't do anything for AML/BSA.

00:11:48.880 --> 00:11:49.328
It has almost no legal protections.

00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:57.740
So no, the banks will not accept it that way.

00:11:57.740 --> 00:12:02.600
They and the ABA, the small banks, the credit unions, not just the big guys.

00:12:02.600 --> 00:12:26.872
I'm not worried about stablecoin, but if it happened, I'm telling you, I would have nothing to do with it, and it would eventually blow up on its own.

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:30.217
Okay.

00:12:30.217 --> 00:12:39.600
But that's my personal thing, but I do understand the concern of all the other banks.

00:12:39.600 --> 00:12:42.013
So, well, the markup is coming.

00:12:52.480 --> 00:12:52.693
I mean, what are you going to do about it?

00:12:52.693 --> 00:12:53.333
It is.

00:12:53.333 --> 00:12:54.186
We'll fight it.

00:12:58.399 --> 00:12:58.639
If we lose, we lose and we'll live.

00:12:58.639 --> 00:12:59.839
Yeah.

00:12:59.839 --> 00:13:01.040
Okay.

00:13:01.040 --> 00:13:03.947
But it will be fought.

00:13:03.947 --> 00:13:13.067
This will not be—no one's going to bow down to this guy, okay, or that company.

00:13:13.067 --> 00:13:22.208
But he's the only one, and he's spending hundreds of millions of dollars in Washington on this thing.

00:13:22.208 --> 00:13:24.079
He said he's representing the whole bleeped it.

00:13:24.079 --> 00:13:25.639
Good job.

00:13:31.246 --> 00:13:31.611
You got it.

00:13:31.611 --> 00:13:34.462
I knew he'd say he dropped a bad word.

00:13:34.462 --> 00:13:36.119
And then she's saying it.

00:13:36.119 --> 00:13:36.959
Okay.

00:13:47.920 --> 00:13:48.206
So, go ahead.

00:13:48.491 --> 00:13:52.160
This is some competition for them.

00:13:58.353 --> 00:13:58.639
They view it as competition that will hurt their ability to sustain the deposits they need to make loans.

00:13:58.639 --> 00:13:59.990
I disagree with that.

00:13:59.990 --> 00:14:08.525
They want changes that actually would go back to the Genius Act we passed last summer and make changes to it.

00:14:23.611 --> 00:14:24.000
I think that they should embrace digital assets.

00:14:25.653 --> 00:14:27.429
It is going to be part of the financial products they can offer in the future.

00:14:33.360 --> 00:14:33.600
We're going to have a digital dollar, a digital Bitcoin, and digital alternative coins.

00:14:35.340 --> 00:14:38.220
It's going to be a new financial landscape and I'd like to see the traditional banking industry embrace it instead of fight it.

00:14:43.320 --> 00:14:43.759
So, the votes—yeah.

00:14:43.759 --> 00:14:46.720
Do you remember you showed me that one?

00:14:56.613 --> 00:14:56.906
I believe it was this one.

00:14:56.906 --> 00:14:57.449
Yes.

00:14:57.449 --> 00:15:00.680
First, your reaction to those comments from Jamie Dimon and Maria.

00:15:00.680 --> 00:15:03.120
Well, we have a lot of respect for Jamie Dimon.

00:15:03.120 --> 00:15:08.632
He's—and JP Morgan's an excellent bank.

00:15:08.632 --> 00:15:25.786
In fact, they're our bank and they've worked with us and stayed by our side even through the Biden administration when the Biden regulators were trying to force banks to debank the crypto sector.

00:15:25.786 --> 00:15:29.093
We have a number of partnerships underway with them.

00:15:29.093 --> 00:15:31.619
We work with them around the world.

00:15:32.639 --> 00:15:34.160
So, we think well of Jamie Dimon and of JP Morgan.

00:15:34.160 --> 00:15:46.533
We have a good partnership with them, but at the end of the day, public policy is about the right outcome for the American people and I'm confident Congress is going to do that.

00:15:59.939 --> 00:16:00.959
The Clarity Act is a really strong bill that creates important consumer protections, but also allows the financial system to become more responsive to the average American.

00:16:02.923 --> 00:16:13.656
And I think that's a great objective, and I'm excited that we're very close to getting the bill on the floor and then ultimately to the president's desk.

00:16:13.656 --> 00:16:20.731
How confident are you that it's going to pass the Senate?

00:16:20.731 --> 00:16:26.347
Look, I feel very good about it.

00:16:26.347 --> 00:16:30.539
I think the Republican caucus is pretty unified.

00:16:30.869 --> 00:16:39.097
The president's been putting his shoulder into this and there's a very large group of Democrats who want to get this done.

00:16:39.097 --> 00:16:47.519
We got about 80 Democrats in the House who voted for this, and I think we'll get a proportional number in the Senate.

00:16:47.519 --> 00:16:50.480
Crypto, interestingly, has actually become the most bipartisan issue in Washington.

00:16:53.725 --> 00:16:55.302
It was probably the singular bipartisan achievement of last year.

00:17:23.839 --> 00:17:24.388
And I think clarity will be the big bipartisan achievement of 2026 going into the midterms and that's pretty exciting.

00:17:24.388 --> 00:17:28.811
You say that this is crypto's Dodd-Frank moment.

00:17:28.811 --> 00:17:31.440
What do you mean by that?

00:17:31.440 --> 00:17:44.194
Well, this will be actually the biggest financial regulatory bill that Congress has done in quite some time, certainly since Dodd-Frank.

00:17:44.194 --> 00:17:50.240
But what this does actually is it creates clarity for the crypto sector.

00:17:50.240 --> 00:18:04.373
But interestingly, notwithstanding the concerns from the banks, it actually creates a broad range of new powers for the banks.

00:18:07.417 --> 00:18:17.691
In fact, this will be the first piece of legislation since the '90s that gives the banks new authorization to get into the crypto space.

00:18:17.691 --> 00:18:20.746
I know JP Morgan wants to get into it.

00:18:20.746 --> 00:18:25.097
Every other big bank wants to get into the crypto sector.

00:18:25.097 --> 00:18:26.640
We welcome their entry.

00:18:26.640 --> 00:18:36.080
We work with many of them and helping them build the services that they want to offer their customers.

00:18:36.080 --> 00:18:38.627
So it's a big, important legislation.

00:18:38.627 --> 00:18:42.213
It's transformational in its nature, and—I mean, you get the gist.

00:18:42.213 --> 00:18:45.931
I mean, he talks for a little bit so it's boring.

00:18:45.931 --> 00:18:47.120
Bitcoin is now.

00:18:47.120 --> 00:18:47.919
Okay.

00:18:47.919 --> 00:18:48.623
Next.

00:18:48.623 --> 00:18:49.679
Anything else?

00:19:00.160 --> 00:19:00.560
And then they're saying June they would adopt it, cross that.

00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:01.269
Okay.

00:19:01.269 --> 00:19:07.340
On the 25 plus banks going live by June using crypto for 24/7 cross-border payments.

00:19:07.340 --> 00:19:08.200
Okay.

00:19:08.200 --> 00:19:09.059
Next.

00:19:18.880 --> 00:19:19.246
And then you have the mosquitoes.

00:19:19.246 --> 00:19:20.709
Then you have—okay.

